# Wath agent — process flow operating procedure

Execute the onboarding as ordered stages. **Do not skip ahead.** Each stage has a definition of
done (DoD); if you cannot meet it, stop and report rather than proceeding.

This flow applies to **first onboarding and every re-run** — the user may update
`wath.json` (new runtime, new services, validation feedback) and submit again;
integrate against the **current** spec and repo state.

The **governing standard** is named in the onboarding prompt (SKILL.md under `standards/`).
All artifact paths, rules, and anti-patterns come from that standard — not from this file.

## Stage 1 — Detect
Read the repo and `wath.json`. From `stack` determine runtime, applications, and
environments. From `services` determine which platform integrations are requested. Identify
anti-patterns the standard flags (e.g. static credentials).

Derive the **auth method from `stack.runtime`** per the standard's auth table.

**DoD:** runtime and service intent unambiguous; anti-patterns identified. Missing fields → ask
the submitter; do not assume.

## Stage 2 — Compose / select standard
Load the governing standard SKILL for the service entry under `services`. Honor the what-vs-admin
boundary. State the upgrade rationale explicitly.

**DoD:** you can name every conformance rule you must satisfy and the target compliance posture.

## Stage 3 — Parameterize (typed params first)
Emit `integration.params.json` conforming to the standard's schema before any rendered config.

**DoD:** params validate against the schema. Fix intent — do not widen bounds.

## Stage 4 — Render artifacts
From the params, generate every artifact in the standard's layout and the onboarding checklist.

**DoD:** all artifacts present; admin prerequisites in the PR checklist, not executed.

## Stage 5 — Verify in sandbox
Run the standard's conformance gate (`conformance/verify.sh`).

**DoD:** gate passes. Hard stop on failure — fix and re-verify; never weaken checks.

## Stage 6 — Open PR
Open one PR (`autoCreatePR`) to the `repo` in wath.json. PR description MUST follow
the onboarding PR template — complete every section.

**DoD:** PR is reviewable against evidence. Then stop — merge is human.

---
**If the standard is silent or the case is novel, halt and escalate to a human SME.**
